# Changelog

## [0.8.0] - 2020-09-18

### Changed
- made converter to singleton to avoid conflicts


## [0.7.3] - 2020-08-23

### Changed
- update requirements


## [0.7.2] - 2020-04-18

### Changed
- update requirements


## [0.7.1] - 2020-03-29

### Changed
- update requirements
- restructure test-files


## [0.7.0] - 2020-01-18

### Changed
- parser-method to be consistent to other repos


## [0.6.2] - 2020-01-05

### Fixed
- if for-loops or if-conditons were at the beginning a the string, the parser had failed.


## [0.6.1] - 2019-12-30

### Changed
- made api thread-save

### Fixed
- some unhandled key-words within the jinja2-string


## [0.6.0] - 2019-11-24

### Chnaged/Fixed
- reworked parser grammar, because it was limited to very simple cases


## [0.5.1] - 2019-11-22

### Changed
- udpate value-range from int to long


## [0.5.0] - 2019-11-02

### Changed
- renamed repo from `libKitsuneJinja2` to `libKitsunemimiJinja2`


## [0.4.0] - 2019-10-20

## Added
- new convert-method for API
- libKitsuneJson as requirement (not only for tests anymore)

### Changed
- update for libKitsuneCommon 0.6.0
- update include-style


## [0.3.0] - 2019-09-22

### Added
- content for Readme
- build-script

### Changed
- return-value of the public convert method was slightly changed
- internal data-representation was changed into a more explicit structure to be better expandable


## [0.2.0] - 2019-08-17

### Changed
- changed file-names for better readable


## [0.1.1] - 2019-08-11

### Changed
- update for libKitsuneCommon 0.2.0 and libKitsuneJson 0.2.0


## [0.1.0] - 2019-08-04

### Added
- basic jinja2-support with simple replacements, if-conditions and for-loops
- can convert jinja2-templates together with a json-tree to a normal string
